  "prompt": "Is TCS good for a first company?",
  "response": "TCS (Tata Consultancy Services) can be a good first company for many reasons:\n\nPros:\n1. Large, stable multinational company\n2. Good brand reputation\n3. Structured training programs\n4. Opportunities for skill development\n5. Diverse work environments\n6. Global exposure\n7. Competitive entry-level salaries\n8. Strong HR policies\n9. Potential for international assignments\n\nPotential Cons:\n1. Can feel bureaucratic\n2. May have less personalized attention\n3. Work can sometimes be routine\n4. High employee turnover\n5. Potentially lower salary compared to product companies\n6. Large teams might limit individual visibility\n\nRecommendation:\n- Good for freshers wanting structured learning\n- Excellent for initial career growth\n- Great for building foundational IT skills\n- Recommended for those seeking stability\n\nBest suited for:\n- IT/Software engineering graduates\n- Those wanting corporate experience\n- People interested in service-based consulting\n\nIndividual experiences can vary, so research current employee reviews and talk to current/former employees for more insights.",
